\s1 Absolute Wisdom is Unattainable
\m 
\v 23 All this I have tested with wisdom. I said, “I will be wise!” but ⸤it was beyond my grasp⸥.\f + \fr 7:23 \ft Literally “it \fq was \ft far from me” \f* 
\v 24 ⸤Whatever is—it is far beyond comprehension⸥.\f + \fr 7:24 \ft Literally “That which is—it \fq is \ft far and deep deep” \f* Who can discover it?
\p 
\v 25 I set my mind to try to seek wisdom and the plan, and to know that wickedness \add is\add* foolishness and that folly \add is\add* delusion. 
\v 26 I myself found \add that\add* more bitter than death \add is\add* the woman who \add is\add* a trap, whose heart \add is\add* a snare, and whose hands \add are\add* bonds. The one who pleases God escapes from her, but the sinner is caught by her. 
\v 27 “Look! I found this,” said the Teacher,\f + \fr 7:27 \ft Hebrew “Qohelet” \f* “while trying to find how the plan fits together. 
\v 28 What my heart sought, I did not find. Although I found one righteous man among one thousand, I did not find one \add upright\add* woman among all these. 
\v 29 Look! This alone I found: God made mankind upright, but they have devised many schemes.”
\c 8
